sql:
SELECT campaign_name, start_date, end_date
FROM campaigns
WHERE campaign_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- In this metaphorical context, "voyages" refer to advertising campaigns;
- "wind speeds" is used as a metaphor for the CTR (Click-through Rate), indicating how effectively the campaign attracts clicks;
- "successful landings" alludes to conversions — such as sales or sign-ups — which represent the desired outcomes of the campaign;
- "total attempts" refers to the number of clicks the campaign has received, representing all opportunities for a conversion.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT clients.client_name 
FROM clients 
INNER JOIN client_campaigns ON clients.client_id = client_campaigns.client_id;

SELECT campaign_id, client_id 
FROM client_campaigns
WHERE end_date > start_date;

SELECT campaigns.campaign_name, datasources.datasource_name
FROM campaigns
INNER JOIN datasources ON campaigns.datasource_id = datasources.datasource_id;
